{
  "texts": [
    "Like Davidson, Anscombe begins her account of the conditions for intentional agency with a discussion of the conditions under which we describe an agent as acting with an intention.",
    "Famously, she characterises intentional actions as those to which '\"a certain sense of the question 'Why?'\" applies (Anscombe, 2000, p. 9).",
    "Answers to this kind of 'Why?'",
    "question are what Davidson calls rationalisations (see §4.1).",
    "They aim to make actions intelligible in light of their agent's reasons."
  ]
}